CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 25, 1953, p. 20, reads: "WINS CARNEGIE TECH BAND POLL AGAIN - When Walt Harper 's orchestra won the poll for the best band for the second straight year at Carnegie Tech, Delta Tau Delta Sorority [Fraternity] honored the band at a dance held in Jacktown Hotel. At the affair, Walt Harper and his drummer, Harold Lee, are shown with members of the sorority and other fraternities on the Tech campus. Walt Harper's band will play a return engagement at the school on May 15, at the May festival.  On May 16, they will travel to Edinboro State Teachers College for a return engagement."
TitMainTitle: Women seated at table with drinks, surrounded by Delta Tau Delta Fraternity members, drummer Harold "Brushes" Lee, and Walt Harper in center, for Carnegie Tech dance in Jacktown Hotel
